  "texts": [
    "Then h g (Y) ⊑ ′ h g (X) by ⊑-forth, which with h g [X] ∈ X ′ and the persistence of X ′ with respect to ⊑ ′ implies h g (Y) ∈ X ′, so Y ∈ h -1 g [X ′].",
    "To show that h -1 g [X ′] satisfies refinability with respect to ⊑, observe that if X ̸ ∈ h -1 g [X ′], so h g (X) ̸ ∈ X ′, then by refinability for X ′ with respect to ⊑ ′, there is a Y ′ ⊑ ′ h g (X) such that (a) for all Y ′′ ⊑ ′ Y ′, Y ′′ ̸ ∈ X ′.",
    "Given Y ′ ⊑ ′ h g (X) and ⊑-back, there is a Y ⊑ X such that h g (Y) ⊑ ′ Y ′.",
    "Then for any Z ⊑ Y, we have h g (Z) ⊑ ′ h g (Y) ⊑ ′ Y ′ by ⊑-forth, so h g (Z) ̸ ∈ X ′ by (a), so Z ̸ ∈ h -1 g [X].",
    "Thus, we have shown that ifX ̸ ∈ h -1 g [X ′], then there is a Y ⊑ X such that for all Z ⊑ Y, Z ̸ ∈ h -1 g [X ′], so h -1 g [X ′] satisfies refinability with respect to ⊑.Next, to show that if h is surjective, then h g is a strong embedding from A f to A ′ f, we need only add to the proof of part 2 above that for all X ∈ P f = RO(S, ⊑), there is anX ′ ∈ P ′ f = RO(S ′, ⊑ ′) such that h g [X] = h g [S] ∩ X ′."
